{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":833,"text":"So in the oasis of \nintelligentsia that is TED,"},{"time":6567,"text":"I stand here before you this evening"},{"time":9285,"text":"as an expert in dragging heavy\nstuff around cold places."},{"time":15159,"text":"I've been leading polar expeditions \nfor most of my adult life,"},{"time":18145,"text":"and last month, my teammate \nTarka L'Herpiniere and I"},{"time":21847,"text":"finished the most ambitious \nexpedition I've ever attempted."},{"time":27025,"text":"In fact, it feels like I've been\ntransported straight here"},{"time":30014,"text":"from four months in the middle of nowhere,"},{"time":32666,"text":"mostly grunting and swearing, \nstraight to the TED stage."},{"time":37754,"text":"So you can imagine that's a transition\nthat hasn't been entirely seamless."},{"time":41935,"text":"One of the interesting side effects"},{"time":43815,"text":"seems to be that my short-term\nmemory is entirely shot."},{"time":46403,"text":"So I've had to write some notes"},{"time":48665,"text":"to avoid too much grunting and swearing\nin the next 17 minutes."},{"time":53363,"text":"This is the first talk I've given\nabout this expedition,"},{"time":56211,"text":"and while we weren't sequencing genomes\nor building space telescopes,"},{"time":61690,"text":"this is a story about giving everything\nwe had to achieve something"},{"time":66474,"text":"that hadn't been done before."},{"time":68310,"text":"So I hope in that you might \nfind some food for thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72455,"text":"It was a journey, an \nexpedition in Antarctica,"},{"time":76066,"text":"the coldest, windiest, driest and\nhighest altitude continent on Earth."},{"time":80757,"text":"It's a fascinating place.\nIt's a huge place."},{"time":82804,"text":"It's twice the size of Australia,"},{"time":85119,"text":"a continent that is the same size\nas China and India put together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90220,"text":"As an aside, I have experienced \n"},{"time":92088,"text":"an interesting phenomenon\nin the last few days,"},{"time":94312,"text":"something that I expect Chris Hadfield\nmay get at TED in a few years' time,"},{"time":98089,"text":"conversations that go something like this:"},{"time":100144,"text":"\"Oh, Antarctica. Awesome."},{"time":101767,"text":"My husband and I did Antarctica\nwith Lindblad for our anniversary.\""},{"time":107604,"text":"Or, \"Oh cool, did you go there\nfor the marathon?\""},{"time":110951,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114445,"text":"Our journey was, in fact,\n69 marathons back to back"},{"time":118485,"text":"in 105 days, an 1,800-mile round trip\non foot from the coast of Antarctica"},{"time":124476,"text":"to the South Pole and back again."},{"time":127247,"text":"In the process, we broke the record\n"},{"time":129491,"text":"for the longest human-powered polar\njourney in history by more than 400 miles."},{"time":135087,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":139498,"text":"For those of you from the Bay Area,"},{"time":141913,"text":"it was the same as walking from \nhere to San Francisco,"},{"time":146030,"text":"then turning around\nand walking back again."},{"time":148908,"text":"So as camping trips go, it was a long one,"},{"time":153827,"text":"and one I've seen summarized \nmost succinctly here"},{"time":156994,"text":"on the hallowed pages \nof Business Insider Malaysia."},{"time":160720,"text":"[\"Two Explorers Just Completed A Polar Expedition \nThat Killed Everyone The Last Time It Was Attempted\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":166247,"text":"Chris Hadfield talked so eloquently"},{"time":168917,"text":"about fear and about the odds of success,\nand indeed the odds of survival."},{"time":174139,"text":"Of the nine people in history that had\nattempted this journey before us,"},{"time":178019,"text":"none had made it to the pole and back,"},{"time":180712,"text":"and five had died in the process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184590,"text":"This is Captain Robert Falcon Scott."},{"time":187237,"text":"He led the last team\nto attempt this expedition."},{"time":190000,"text":"Scott and his rival Sir Ernest Shackleton,"},{"time":192438,"text":"over the space of a decade,"},{"time":195154,"text":"both led expeditions battling to become\nthe first to reach the South Pole,"},{"time":199427,"text":"to chart and map\nthe interior of Antarctica,"},{"time":202446,"text":"a place we knew less about, at the time,"},{"time":204581,"text":"than the surface of the moon,"},{"time":206485,"text":"because we could see\nthe moon through telescopes."},{"time":208830,"text":"Antarctica was, for the most part,\na century ago, uncharted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212964,"text":"Some of you may know the story."},{"time":214475,"text":"Scott's last expedition, the \nTerra Nova Expedition in 1910,"},{"time":217288,"text":"started as a giant\nsiege-style approach."},{"time":219802,"text":"He had a big team using ponies,"},{"time":222031,"text":"using dogs, using petrol-driven tractors,"},{"time":224778,"text":"dropping multiple, pre-positioned\ndepots of food and fuel"},{"time":228175,"text":"through which Scott's final team of five\nwould travel to the Pole,"},{"time":231883,"text":"where they would turn around and ski \nback to the coast again on foot."},{"time":235187,"text":"Scott and his final team of five"},{"time":237599,"text":"arrived at the South Pole \nin January 1912"},{"time":241284,"text":"to find they had been beaten to it\nby a Norwegian team led by Roald Amundsen,"},{"time":246274,"text":"who rode on dogsled."},{"time":247908,"text":"Scott's team ended up on foot."},{"time":249997,"text":"And for more than a century\nthis journey has remained unfinished."},{"time":254595,"text":"Scott's team of five died \non the return journey."},{"time":257520,"text":"And for the last decade,"},{"time":259633,"text":"I've been asking myself why that is."},{"time":262954,"text":"How come this has remained \nthe high-water mark?"},{"time":266246,"text":"Scott's team covered 1,600 miles on foot."},{"time":268596,"text":"No one's come close to that ever since."},{"time":270497,"text":"So this is the high-water mark \nof human endurance,"},{"time":273318,"text":"human endeavor, \nhuman athletic achievement"},{"time":275839,"text":"in arguably the harshest climate on Earth."},{"time":278510,"text":"It was as if the marathon record"},{"time":281018,"text":"has remained unbroken since 1912."},{"time":284037,"text":"And of course some strange and \npredictable combination of curiosity,"},{"time":289145,"text":"stubbornness, and probably hubris"},{"time":291095,"text":"led me to thinking I might be the man\nto try to finish the job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295182,"text":"Unlike Scott's expedition,\nthere were just two of us,"},{"time":298873,"text":"and we set off from the coast\nof Antarctica in October last year,"},{"time":301996,"text":"dragging everything ourselves,"},{"time":304214,"text":"a process Scott called \"man-hauling.\""},{"time":306814,"text":"When I say it was like walking from\nhere to San Francisco and back,"},{"time":309837,"text":"I actually mean it was like dragging\nsomething that weighs a shade more"},{"time":313214,"text":"than the heaviest ever NFL player."},{"time":315638,"text":"Our sledges weighed 200 kilos,"},{"time":317681,"text":"or 440 pounds each at the start,"},{"time":320746,"text":"the same weights that the weakest\nof Scott's ponies pulled."},{"time":325020,"text":"Early on, we averaged 0.5 miles per hour."},{"time":328200,"text":"Perhaps the reason no one had \nattempted this journey until now,"},{"time":331887,"text":"in more than a century,"},{"time":333145,"text":"was that no one had been quite\nstupid enough to try."},{"time":338418,"text":"And while I can't claim we were exploring"},{"time":340437,"text":"in the genuine Edwardian\nsense of the word —"},{"time":343454,"text":"we weren't naming any mountains\nor mapping any uncharted valleys —"},{"time":347192,"text":"I think we were stepping into uncharted\nterritory in a human sense."},{"time":351573,"text":"Certainly, if in the future we learn\nthere is an area of the human brain"},{"time":354962,"text":"that lights up when one curses oneself,"},{"time":358779,"text":"I won't be at all surprised."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361945,"text":"You've heard that the average American\nspends 90 percent of their time indoors."},{"time":365997,"text":"We didn't go indoors\nfor nearly four months."},{"time":369253,"text":"We didn't see a sunset either."},{"time":371495,"text":"It was 24-hour daylight."},{"time":373151,"text":"Living conditions were quite spartan."},{"time":375306,"text":"I changed my underwear \nthree times in 105 days"},{"time":380148,"text":"and Tarka and I shared \n30 square feet on the canvas."},{"time":384072,"text":"Though we did have some technology\nthat Scott could never have imagined."},{"time":388813,"text":"And we blogged live every evening\nfrom the tent via a laptop"},{"time":392180,"text":"and a custom-made satellite transmitter,"},{"time":394225,"text":"all of which were solar-powered:"},{"time":396085,"text":"we had a flexible photovoltaic\npanel over the tent."},{"time":398482,"text":"And the writing was important to me."},{"time":401940,"text":"As a kid, I was inspired by the \nliterature of adventure and exploration,"},{"time":408493,"text":"and I think we've all seen\nhere this week"},{"time":411021,"text":"the importance and \nthe power of storytelling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415265,"text":"So we had some 21st-century gear,"},{"time":417081,"text":"but the reality is that the \nchallenges that Scott faced"},{"time":419868,"text":"were the same that we faced:"},{"time":421865,"text":"those of the weather and of \nwhat Scott called glide,"},{"time":425603,"text":"the amount of friction between\nthe sledges and the snow."},{"time":428951,"text":"The lowest wind chill \nwe experienced was in the -70s,"},{"time":432801,"text":"and we had zero visibility,\nwhat's called white-out,"},{"time":435378,"text":"for much of our journey."},{"time":438391,"text":"We traveled up and down one of the largest"},{"time":440742,"text":"and most dangerous glaciers\nin the world, the Beardmore glacier."},{"time":443955,"text":"It's 110 miles long; most of its surface\nis what's called blue ice."},{"time":447381,"text":"You can see it's a beautiful, \nshimmering steel-hard blue surface"},{"time":450979,"text":"covered with thousands \nand thousands of crevasses,"},{"time":454817,"text":"these deep cracks in the glacial ice \nup to 200 feet deep."},{"time":458798,"text":"Planes can't land here,"},{"time":460315,"text":"so we were at the most risk,"},{"time":463775,"text":"technically, when we had the slimmest\nchance of being rescued."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468219,"text":"We got to the South Pole\nafter 61 days on foot,"},{"time":472115,"text":"with one day off for bad weather,"},{"time":474694,"text":"and I'm sad to say, it was\nsomething of an anticlimax."},{"time":477261,"text":"There's a permanent American base,"},{"time":479726,"text":"the Amundsen-Scott South Pole Station\nat the South Pole."},{"time":483044,"text":"They have an airstrip,\nthey have a canteen,"},{"time":484995,"text":"they have hot showers,"},{"time":486448,"text":"they have a post office, a tourist shop,\n"},{"time":488353,"text":"a basketball court that doubles\nas a movie theater."},{"time":492091,"text":"So it's a bit different these days,"},{"time":494066,"text":"and there are also acres of junk."},{"time":495862,"text":"I think it's a marvelous thing\n"},{"time":497292,"text":"that humans can exist\n365 days of the year"},{"time":502586,"text":"with hamburgers and hot showers\nand movie theaters,"},{"time":506131,"text":"but it does seem to produce\na lot of empty cardboard boxes."},{"time":508887,"text":"You can see on the left of \nthis photograph,"},{"time":510949,"text":"several square acres of junk"},{"time":512384,"text":"waiting to be flown out\nfrom the South Pole."},{"time":514897,"text":"But there is also a pole at the South Pole,"},{"time":518929,"text":"and we got there on foot, unassisted,"},{"time":522325,"text":"unsupported, by the hardest route,"},{"time":523971,"text":"900 miles in record time,"},{"time":526316,"text":"dragging more weight\nthan anyone in history."},{"time":528364,"text":"And if we'd stopped there \nand flown home,"},{"time":530333,"text":"which would have been\nthe eminently sensible thing to do,"},{"time":533467,"text":"then my talk would end here"},{"time":535348,"text":"and it would end something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538938,"text":"If you have the right team around you,\nthe right tools, the right technology,"},{"time":543743,"text":"and if you have enough self-belief\nand enough determination,"},{"time":547481,"text":"then anything is possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552656,"text":"But then we turned around,"},{"time":555289,"text":"and this is where things get interesting."},{"time":558048,"text":"High on the Antarctic plateau,"},{"time":560842,"text":"over 10,000 feet, it's very windy,\nvery cold, very dry, we were exhausted."},{"time":564841,"text":"We'd covered 35 marathons,"},{"time":566711,"text":"we were only halfway,"},{"time":568297,"text":"and we had a safety net, of course,"},{"time":570328,"text":"of ski planes and satellite phones"},{"time":572452,"text":"and live, 24-hour tracking beacons\nthat didn't exist for Scott,"},{"time":576515,"text":"but in hindsight,"},{"time":578257,"text":"rather than making our lives easier,"},{"time":580323,"text":"the safety net actually allowed us"},{"time":582482,"text":"to cut things very fine indeed,"},{"time":586337,"text":"to sail very close to our absolute\nlimits as human beings."},{"time":590104,"text":"And it is an exquisite form of torture"},{"time":593577,"text":"to exhaust yourself to the point\nof starvation day after day"},{"time":596414,"text":"while dragging a sledge\nfull of food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600686,"text":"For years, I'd been writing glib lines\nin sponsorship proposals"},{"time":604613,"text":"about pushing the limits\nof human endurance,"},{"time":607724,"text":"but in reality, that was \na very frightening place to be indeed."},{"time":612136,"text":"We had, before we'd got to the Pole,"},{"time":614045,"text":"two weeks of almost permanent\nheadwind, which slowed us down."},{"time":617509,"text":"As a result, we'd had several days\nof eating half rations."},{"time":620159,"text":"We had a finite amount of food\nin the sledges to make this journey,"},{"time":622878,"text":"so we were trying to string that out"},{"time":624880,"text":"by reducing our intake to half \nthe calories we should have been eating."},{"time":628793,"text":"As a result, we both became\nincreasingly hypoglycemic —"},{"time":632412,"text":"we had low blood sugar \nlevels day after day —"},{"time":635236,"text":"and increasingly susceptible\nto the extreme cold."},{"time":639994,"text":"Tarka took this photo of me one evening"},{"time":642097,"text":"after I'd nearly passed out\nwith hypothermia."},{"time":644227,"text":"We both had repeated bouts of hypothermia,\nsomething I hadn't experienced before,"},{"time":649035,"text":"and it was very humbling indeed."},{"time":650746,"text":"As much as you might\nlike to think, as I do,"},{"time":654414,"text":"that you're the kind\nof person who doesn't quit,"},{"time":656670,"text":"that you'll go down swinging,"},{"time":658664,"text":"hypothermia doesn't leave you much choice."},{"time":660916,"text":"You become utterly incapacitated."},{"time":663726,"text":"It's like being a drunk toddler."},{"time":666907,"text":"You become pathetic."},{"time":668880,"text":"I remember just wanting\nto lie down and quit."},{"time":672999,"text":"It was a peculiar, peculiar feeling,"},{"time":675173,"text":"and a real surprise to me\nto be debilitated to that degree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680412,"text":"And then we ran out of food completely,"},{"time":684894,"text":"46 miles short of the first of the depots"},{"time":688352,"text":"that we'd laid on our outward journey."},{"time":690217,"text":"We'd laid 10 depots of food,"},{"time":691560,"text":"literally burying food and fuel,\nfor our return journey —"},{"time":694277,"text":"the fuel was for a cooker so you\ncould melt snow to get water —"},{"time":697554,"text":"and I was forced to make the decision\nto call for a resupply flight,"},{"time":703361,"text":"a ski plane carrying eight days of food\nto tide us over that gap."},{"time":707930,"text":"They took 12 hours to reach us\nfrom the other side of Antarctica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711289,"text":"Calling for that plane was one of \nthe toughest decisions of my life."},{"time":714998,"text":"And I sound like a bit of a fraud\nstanding here now with a sort of belly."},{"time":718474,"text":"I've put on 30 pounds\nin the last three weeks."},{"time":721314,"text":"Being that hungry has left\nan interesting mental scar,"},{"time":724389,"text":"which is that I've been hoovering up\nevery hotel buffet that I can find."},{"time":728996,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":730774,"text":"But we were genuinely quite hungry,\nand in quite a bad way."},{"time":736468,"text":"I don't regret calling\nfor that plane for a second,"},{"time":738909,"text":"because I'm still standing here alive,"},{"time":740911,"text":"with all digits intact, \ntelling this story."},{"time":742971,"text":"But getting external assistance like that\nwas never part of the plan,"},{"time":747709,"text":"and it's something my ego\nis still struggling with."},{"time":750913,"text":"This was the biggest dream I've ever had,"},{"time":753955,"text":"and it was so nearly perfect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756967,"text":"On the way back down to the coast,"},{"time":758648,"text":"our crampons — they're \nthe spikes on our boots"},{"time":760839,"text":"that we have for traveling\nover this blue ice on the glacier —"},{"time":763765,"text":"broke on the top of the Beardmore."},{"time":765420,"text":"We still had 100 miles to go downhill"},{"time":767185,"text":"on very slippery rock-hard blue ice."},{"time":769419,"text":"They needed repairing almost every hour."},{"time":771810,"text":"To give you an idea of scale,"},{"time":773761,"text":"this is looking down towards the mouth\nof the Beardmore Glacier."},{"time":776758,"text":"You could fit the entirety of Manhattan\nin the gap on the horizon."},{"time":780233,"text":"That's 20 miles between\nMount Hope and Mount Kiffin."},{"time":783447,"text":"I've never felt as small \nas I did in Antarctica."},{"time":789680,"text":"When we got down\nto the mouth of the glacier,"},{"time":791785,"text":"we found fresh snow had obscured\nthe dozens of deep crevasses."},{"time":796431,"text":"One of Shackleton's men described\ncrossing this sort of terrain"},{"time":799381,"text":"as like walking over the glass roof\nof a railway station."},{"time":804375,"text":"We fell through more times\nthan I can remember,"},{"time":807289,"text":"usually just putting a ski\nor a boot through the snow."},{"time":810721,"text":"Occasionally we went in all \nthe way up to our armpits,"},{"time":813324,"text":"but thankfully never deeper than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816767,"text":"And less than five weeks ago,\nafter 105 days,"},{"time":820947,"text":"we crossed this oddly \ninauspicious finish line,"},{"time":824522,"text":"the coast of Ross Island \non the New Zealand side of Antarctica."},{"time":827544,"text":"You can see the ice in the foreground"},{"time":829694,"text":"and the sort of rubbly rock behind that."},{"time":832556,"text":"Behind us lay an unbroken \nski trail of nearly 1,800 miles."},{"time":836358,"text":"We'd made the longest ever\npolar journey on foot,"},{"time":838866,"text":"something I'd been dreaming \nof doing for a decade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843256,"text":"And looking back,"},{"time":845271,"text":"I still stand by all the things"},{"time":847666,"text":"I've been saying for years"},{"time":849248,"text":"about the importance of goals"},{"time":851367,"text":"and determination and self-belief,"},{"time":854809,"text":"but I'll also admit that I hadn't given\nmuch thought to what happens"},{"time":859520,"text":"when you reach the all-consuming goal"},{"time":863432,"text":"that you've dedicated \nmost of your adult life to,"},{"time":866750,"text":"and the reality is that I'm \nstill figuring that bit out."},{"time":870330,"text":"As I said, there are very few\nsuperficial signs that I've been away."},{"time":873931,"text":"I've put on 30 pounds."},{"time":875382,"text":"I've got some very faint, probably \ncovered in makeup now, frostbite scars."},{"time":878910,"text":"I've got one on my nose, one on \neach cheek, from where the goggles are,"},{"time":882383,"text":"but inside I am a very \ndifferent person indeed."},{"time":887128,"text":"If I'm honest,"},{"time":889625,"text":"Antarctica challenged me\nand humbled me so deeply"},{"time":894800,"text":"that I'm not sure I'll ever be able\nto put it into words."},{"time":898503,"text":"I'm still struggling to piece\ntogether my thoughts."},{"time":902603,"text":"That I'm standing here \ntelling this story"},{"time":906248,"text":"is proof that we all can \naccomplish great things,"},{"time":911026,"text":"through ambition, through passion,"},{"time":913180,"text":"through sheer stubbornness,"},{"time":915342,"text":"by refusing to quit,"},{"time":916857,"text":"that if you dream something \nhard enough, as Sting said,"},{"time":919813,"text":"it does indeed come to pass."},{"time":922884,"text":"But I'm also standing here \nsaying, you know what,"},{"time":926230,"text":"that cliche about the journey being \nmore important than the destination?"},{"time":932211,"text":"There's something in that."},{"time":935532,"text":"The closer I got to my finish line,"},{"time":937901,"text":"that rubbly, rocky coast of Ross Island,"},{"time":941657,"text":"the more I started to realize\nthat the biggest lesson"},{"time":944851,"text":"that this very long, very hard walk\nmight be teaching me"},{"time":949431,"text":"is that happiness is not\na finish line,"},{"time":953124,"text":"that for us humans,"},{"time":954694,"text":"the perfection that so many of\nus seem to dream of"},{"time":958170,"text":"might not ever be truly attainable,"},{"time":962250,"text":"and that if we can't feel content\nhere, today, now, on our journeys"},{"time":970716,"text":"amidst the mess and the striving\nthat we all inhabit,"},{"time":975184,"text":"the open loops, \nthe half-finished to-do lists,"},{"time":977904,"text":"the could-do-better-next-times,"},{"time":980756,"text":"then we might never feel it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984055,"text":"A lot of people have asked me, what next?"},{"time":987631,"text":"Right now, I am very happy just recovering\nand in front of hotel buffets."},{"time":994629,"text":"But as Bob Hope put it,"},{"time":998982,"text":"I feel very humble,"},{"time":1001278,"text":"but I think I have the strength\nof character to fight it. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005347,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007297,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}